---
description: Rules for Alembic migration files
globs: "backend/migrations/**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---

## Migration rules

- NEVER edit an existing migration file
- Always create a new one: `alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description"`
- Every schema change needs a migration — never ALTER directly in psql
- Always include a `downgrade()` function that fully reverses the `upgrade()`
- pgvector indexes must use HNSW — never IVFFlat:

  ```python
  # CORRECT
  op.execute("CREATE INDEX ON artifact_chunks USING hnsw (embedding vector_cosine_ops)")

  # WRONG
  op.execute("CREATE INDEX ON artifact_chunks USING ivfflat (embedding vector_cosine_ops)")
  ```

- Foreign keys to studios/software/projects/sections must include ON DELETE CASCADE
